		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">MIMO</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">This article is about MIMO in wireless communication.  For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/MIMO_(disambiguation)" title="MIMO (disambiguation)">MIMO (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:282px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Prinzip_MIMO.png" class="image" title="Understanding of SISO, SIMO, MISO and MIMO"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Prinzip_MIMO.png/280px-Prinzip_MIMO.png" width="280" height="280" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Prinzip_MIMO.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Understanding of SISO, SIMO, MISO and MIMO</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>In <a href="/wiki/Radio" title="Radio">radio</a>, <b>multiple-input and multiple-output</b>, or <b>MIMO</b> (pronounced <i>mee-moh</i>), is the use of multiple antennas at both the transmitter and receiver to improve communication performance. It is one of several forms of <a href="/wiki/Smart_antenna" title="Smart antenna">smart antenna</a> technology.</p>
<p>MIMO technology has attracted attention in <a href="/wiki/Wireless" title="Wireless">wireless</a> communications, since it offers significant increases in data throughput and link range without additional bandwidth or transmit power. It achieves this by higher spectral efficiency (more bits per second per hertz of bandwidth) and link reliability or diversity (reduced fading). Because of these properties, MIMO is a current<sup class="plainlinks noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=MIMO&amp;action=edit" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=MIMO&amp;action=edit" rel="nofollow">[update]</a></sup> theme of international wireless research. (Refer to: <a href="/wiki/MIMO#MIMO_literature" title="MIMO">Research trends in MIMO literature</a>)</p>
